**[1862, 11-14] Ms.A.9.2.31.24**

Joseph Ricketson to Deborah Weston

More on Maggi, who is a combination of Mazzini and Garibaldi.

“I never saw a man so imbued with the spirit of Liberty as Maggi—he has
the principles of Mazzini & the military qualifications of Garibaldi
combined. Should his life be shared, he will probably be promoted.”


